..TEXT:
The first description of the diviners insists upon their
silence and their misery, expressed by tears, the only form of
expression allowed them, given the fact that their necks are twisted,
thus cutting off the possibility of speech.  We are probably meant to
reflect on the fact that their voices, announcing their false
prescriptions were the instruments of their deception of their
clients/victims.
